  "time_ut": 1656999771,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0db8\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0db6\u0dba\u0da7 \u0d86 \u0da2\u0db1\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd2\u0da7 \u0d91\u0dbb\u0dd9\u0dc4\u0dd2\u0dc0 \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0db4\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc2\u0dba\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0ddc\u0db0\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A protest from the opposition against the President who came to the Assembly",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "When President Gotabhaya Rajapaksa was in the Parliament chamber, the members of the Samagi Jana Balawega and the Tamil National Alliance rose from their seats and held up placards saying \"Go Home Gota\" (Gotta go home) and continued to protest. .",
        "Due to this heated situation, Speaker Mahinda Yapa Abeywardena adjourned the House for ten minutes as he could not control the affairs of the House.",
        "This objection of the opposition arose when Prime Minister Ranil Wickramasinghe was making a statement regarding the economic situation of the country.",
        "The president was seen smiling and looking at the members of Samagi Jana Balawega and Tamil National Alliance while they were protesting like this.",
        "While those MPs were protesting like this, the MPs of the ruling party shouted \"we want gota\".",
        "Former Minister SB Dissanayake came close to the President and was seen raising one hand and shouting \"We Want Gota\" continuously.",
        "During this protest, former President Mahinda Rajapaksa raised his hand and said something to the President.",
        "President Gotabhaya Rajapaksa arrived at the Parliament Chamber at around 10.00 am yesterday.",
        "While sitting in their seats and listening to the Prime Minister's speech, the opposition MPs started the agitation.",
        "While the protest was going on, the President was seen leaving the House at around 10:30 am.",
        "A group of MPs and Sergeant-at-Arms Narendra Fernando also traveled with the President.",
        "The first to come forward with the protest sign against the President was Mr. Mujibar Rahman, Colombo District Councilor of Samagi Janabalawega.",
        "After the President left, Mr. Sajith Premadasa, the leader of the opposition, started to make comments, and at that time the members of the ruling party continuously interrupted his speech.",
        "The words \"dog\" \"donkey\" \"fool\" were also exchanged at this time."
      ],
